description: Specifies the key value store resource to add to your account. In your account, the key value store names must be unique. You can also import key value store data in JSON format from an S3 bucket by providing a valid ImportSource that you own.

parameters.name: Name
parameters.description: The name of the key value store. The minimum length is 1 character and the maximum length is 64 characters.

parameters.name: ImportSource
parameters.description: The S3 bucket that provides the source for the import. The source must be in a valid JSON format. The source type of the import source for the key value store. The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the import source for the key value store.

nested_params.name: SourceType
nested_params.description: The source type of the import source for the key value store.

nested_params.name: SourceARN
nested_params.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the import source for the key value store.

nested_items.name: Name
nested_items.description: The name of the key value store.

nested_items.name: Id
nested_items.description: The unique Id for the key value store.

nested_items.name: Comment
nested_items.description: A comment for the key value store.

nested_items.name: ARN
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the key value store.

nested_items.name: Status
nested_items.description: The status of the key value store.

nested_items.name: LastModifiedTime
nested_items.description: The last-modified time of the key value store.

nested_items.name: ETag
nested_items.description: The ETag in the resulting key value store.

nested_items.name: Location
nested_items.description: The location of the resulting key value store.
